{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-docs-post-js","path":"/disabling-autologin/","webpackCompilationHash":"9aa34f7a6bc717b201c4","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"ee54aea7-d138-5ccd-bf34-79af8170af6d","html":"<p>You can disable the automatic login process and force JXOS to display the login message at terminal by disabling the <code class=\"language-text\">NoDM</code> systemd service:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> systemctl disable nodm</code></pre></div>\n<p>and to re-enable it again :</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> dpkg-reconfigure nodm</code></pre></div>\n<p>to completely remove it :</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo apt remove nodm</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Disable AutoLogin"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/disabling-autologin/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/installation-image/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Image Disk File Installation"}},"next":null}}}